## ABSTRACT OF THE DISCLOSURE
A monolithic 3-tier (3T) hardware controller for quantum optomechanics is disclosed. The substrate integrates a memristive crossbar core, an epitaxial photodiode matrix, and a micro-lensed LED array. The controller pre-computes non-Euclidean Poincaré disk space adjustments inside solid-state memory registers. This layout allows the system to continuously calculate particle displacement errors and adjust 3D optical gravity wells at sub-microsecond hardware speeds, enabling low-latency, fault-tolerant adiabatic qubit braiding.
